## AWS Resources (via LocalStack)

This service provisions the following resources through Terraform:

| Resource | Name | Purpose |
|----------|------|---------|
| SQS Queue | `{{SERVICE_NAME}}-queue` | Main event queue (long polling, 1-day retention) |
| SQS DLQ | `{{SERVICE_NAME}}-dlq` | Dead-letter queue (max 3 retries, 14-day retention) |
| SSM Parameter | `/local/{{SERVICE_NAME}}/config` | Runtime config — contains queue URLs |

### Provision resources

```bash
cd terraform
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply -auto-approve
```

### Verify on LocalStack

```bash
# List queues
aws --endpoint-url=http://localhost:4566 sqs list-queues

# Send a test message
aws --endpoint-url=http://localhost:4566 sqs send-message \
  --queue-url http://localhost:4566/000000000000/{{SERVICE_NAME}}-queue \
  --message-body '{"event": "test"}'

# Read SSM config (contains queue URLs)
aws --endpoint-url=http://localhost:4566 ssm get-parameter \
  --name "/local/{{SERVICE_NAME}}/config" --query Parameter.Value
```

